   EARTHQUAKE AFFECTS CHARLESTON, SAN FRANCISCO AND SOUTH CAROLINA
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Although they are a continent apart, the cities of Charleston, S.C., and San Francisco now share a fateful page in the ledger of time.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   They are the scenes of two of the century's costliest, back-to-back natural disasters: Hurricane Hugo and the Bay Area earthquake. Broken glass and other debris left the roadsides lined with cars stopped by flat tires . By contrast the streets in most of San Francisco were passable within a day of the earthquake .
